== Summary ==
This provides the ability to create, edit, and remove images floating on the screen. It is implemented as a wrapper around a sprite, so any sprite actions are applicable.

== Instances ==
Floating Images are created in a script or from the console.
=== Example ===

Example of a definition in a level file (from menu.stl, actually):
<code>
(init-script "
logo <- FloatingImage(\"images/objects/logo/logo.sprite\");
logo.set_anchor_point(ANCHOR_TOP);
logo.set_pos(0, 30);
logo.set_visible(true);
// Suspend (this is needed so that logo doesn't get deleted)
suspend();
")
</code>

The above will create a floating image name "logo", anchor it to the top, set its position, and finally displays it instantaneously. To use this in the console, remove everything before "logo <-" and everything after "set_visible(true);"

== Methods ==
{| class="objectlist"
! class="method"| void set_layer(int layer)
| Sets the layer of this image to <tt>layer</tt>.
|-
! class="method"| int get_layer()
| Returns the current layer of this image.
|-
! class="method"| void set_pos(float x, float  y)
| Sets the position of this image to (x,y)
|-
! class="method"| int get_x()
| Returns the x position of this image.
|-
! class="method"| int get_y()
| Returns the y position of this image.
|-
! class="method"| int get_anchor_point()
| Returns the current anchor point of this image. (See set_anchor_point for a list of values)
|-
! class="method"| void set_anchor_point(int anchor)
| Sets the anchor of this image. One of <tt>ANCHOR_TOP_LEFT</tt>,<tt> ANCHOR_TOP</tt>,<tt> ANCHOR_TOP_RIGHT</tt>,<tt> ANCHOR_LEFT</tt>,<tt> ANCHOR_MIDDLE</tt>,<tt> ANCHOR_RIGHT</tt>,<tt> ANCHOR_BOTTOM_LEFT</tt>,<tt> ANCHOR_BOTTOM</tt>,<tt> or ANCHOR_BOTTOM_RIGHT</tt>.
|-
! class="method"| string get_action()
| Returns the current action of this image. (Only useful for sprites)
|-
! class="method"| set_action(string action)
| Sets the current action of this image. (Only useful for sprites)
|-
! class="method"| bool get_visible()
| Returns the current visibility of this image.
|-
! class="method"| set_visible(bool visible)
| Shows or hides the image abruptly (drastic counterpart to <tt>fade_in</tt> and <tt>fade_out</tt>).
|-
! class="method"| fade_in(float time)
| Fades in this image for the next <tt>time</tt> seconds.
|-
! class="method"| fade_out(float time)
| Just the opposite of <tt>fade_in</tt>.
|}

